MultiStep`\\n    11→- **`--agent <agent>`** -- optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n    12→- **A local artifact path** -- skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n    13→- **CI run reference** -- triggers artifact download instead of local re-runs:\\n    14→  - `latest CI run` / `latest` -- most recent failed E2E run on main\\n    15→  - A GitHub Actions run ID (numeric, e.g., `12345678`)\\n    16→  - A GitHub Actions run URL\\n    17→\\n    18→**CI artifact download:** When a CI run reference is provided, download artifacts using:\\n    19→\\n    20→```bash\\n    21→scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <latest | RUN_ID | RUN_URL>\\n    22→```\\n    23→\\n    24→The script outputs the absolute artifact path as its **last line of stdout** -- capture that and use it as the artifact path for analysis. After downloading, **skip Steps L2-L5** (local re-runs) and go straight to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1), since we're analyzing CI artifacts, not running tests locally.\\n    25→\\n    26→**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n    27→\\n    28→## Step L2: First Run\\n    29→\\n    30→```bash\\n    31→mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    32→```\\n    33→\\n    34→Capture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n    35→\\n    36→## Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n    37→\\n    38→If the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n    39→\\n    40→If the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n    41→\\n    42→## Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n    43→\\n    44→If results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n    45→\\n    46→## Step L5: Collect Results\\n    47→\\n    48→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n    49→\\n    50→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n    51→\\n    52→---\\n    53→\\n    54→## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n    55→\\n    56→### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n    57→\\n    58→For each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/e2e/debug.md` (steps 2-5: console.log -> test source -> entire.log -> deep dive). Collect:\\n    59→- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n    60→- What was expected (from test source)\\n    61→- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n    62→- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n    63→\\n    64→### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n    65→\\n    66→Use **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n    67→\\n    68→#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n    69→\\n    70→| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n    71→|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n    72→| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** -- see below |\\n    73→| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n    74→| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    75→| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    76→| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** -- examine artifacts |\\n    77→\\n    78→**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n    79→- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` -> **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n    80→- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) -> **flaky (test-bug)** -- the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n    81→\\n    82→#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n    83→\\n    84→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n    85→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n    86→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n    87→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n    88→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n    89→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n    90→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n    91→\\n    92→**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n    93→\\n    94→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n    95→\\n    96→**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n    97→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n    98→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n    99→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n   100→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n   101→- Agent produced no output\\n   102→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n   103→- Duration near timeout limit\\n   104→\\n   105→**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n   106→- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors -> test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n   107→- Env vars not propagated to agent session -> tmux/test harness bug\\n   108→- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   109→- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n   110→- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n   111→- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n   112→\\n   113→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   114→\\n   115→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   116→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   117→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   118→\\n   119→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   120→\\n   121→Before reporting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   122→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   123→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   124→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   125→\\n   126→### Step 4: Present Findings Report\\n   127→\\n   128→For each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n   129→\\n   130→```\\n   131→## <TestName> (<agent>) -- <classification>\\n   132→\\n   133→**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n   134→**Evidence:**\\n   135→- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n   136→- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n   137→```\\n   138→\\n   139→For `flaky` failures, include proposed fix description:\\n   140→\\n   141→```\\n   142→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n   143→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n   144→  - Change: <what will be modified>\\n   145→```\\n   146→\\n   147→Common flaky fixes:\\n   148→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   149→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   150→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   151→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   152→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   153→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   154→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   155→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   156→\\n   157→For `real-bug` failures, include root cause analysis:\\n   158→\\n   159→```\\n   160→**Root cause analysis:**\\n   161→  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n   162→  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n   16